Authentication vs Authorization

Authentication is proof that you are who say you when logging in

Authurazation is proof that you are ALLOWED to do what you are trying to do (read-only access trying to modify data).

Base64 encoding vs Encryption

Encoding is not encryption

Encoding allows us to transmit binary data over systems that ues text-based control

Encoding is reversible
